                            <b>Help on Registering</b><p>
                            You must agree to the terms of this board before you can sign up. Please read the terms carefully before clicking on 'I agree'.<p>
If the board administrator requires email verification, your password will be emailed to you. You can change this password at any time by modifying your profile. If you are permitted to choose your own password, make sure it's one that is not easily guessed, and contains at least 5 characters.<p>
You must enter a valid email address, you cannot proceed if the email address is not entered correctly. i.e. you@yourdomain.com, name.name@domain.subdomain.co.uk or similar. You can keep this email address private by clicking on the 'Show Email Adress' 'no' radio button.<p>
The other fields are optional, but you are encouraged to enter as much information as you are comfortable with. The board administrator runs a 'no-spam' policy and all your details are confidentail.<p>
<b>Time Zone</b><br>
You may enter the amount of hours you need to make all the times on the board local to you. You may use a '-' if needed. For example, if you are five hours behind the time on the board, enter '-5'.<p>
<b>Signature</b><br>
You may include a signature to be added to the bottom of every post. You may only have three lines (a line is counted every time you press enter). You may use the ikoncode tags specified, but you may not use HTML.
